content:
They speak for the dead.

The NYPD Crime Scene Unit - several dozen dedicated detectives - gave us a rare and exclusive look behind the yellow tape, at a world even most cops never get to see.

They work sometimes for days at a time, in all kinds of conditions, cataloguing the grisly, stomach turning, nightmare-inducing handiwork of NYC's violent criminals. And if they make a single mistake, a killer can go free.
name: Josh Einiger
title: On the front lines with the NYPD Crime Scene Unit

content:
One year ago, Dave Alter and I watched an endless and heartbreaking caravan of coroner vans gliding in and out of Pulse Orlando, after the worst mass shooting in US history.

A year later, the pain has barely receded. And while the City of Orlando has started to move forward, they'll never move on. 

And they'll never forget.
name: Josh Einiger
